The paper deals with the problem of estimating the size of a weighted set, which is a common problem in machine learning and optimization. The authors introduce a new technique based on Rademacher complexity, which is a well-known concept in machine learning and statistical learning theory. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also applies the proposed method to the problems of calculating the partition function of an Ising model and computing propositional model counts (#SAT), which are problems in artificial intelligence and theoretical computer science. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also involves optimization and probability theory, which are relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory), respectively.
